Rivers State Governor Nyesom Wike has dissolved the State Executive Council (SEC). The governor’s spokesperson Kelvin Ebiri announced the development in a statement released on Tuesday. READ ALSO: 2023: Wike donates N200 million to Kaduna State IDPs Presidency faults Wike’s criticism of state pardon granted Dariye, Nyame 2023: I can remove APC from power, Wike says as he declares for president 2023: Wike, Obaseki in verbal war over control of PDP He said the dissolution of the cabinet was with immediate effect. He added that the Chief of Staff to the governor and his Senior Special Assistant (Protocol) were relieved of their duties. Wike commended the members of the Rivers State Executive Council for their services and contributions to the development of the state and wished them the best in all their future endeavours. He instructed all the former members of his cabinet to hand over to the most senior officers in their respective ministries.